Nigeria Info 99.3 has unveiled plans to build a formidable sports-broadcast army through the launch of the third edition of the ‘Femi and The Gang Fan Battle’. This is in a bid to create a platform that provides sports-loving Nigerians with an avenue to showcase their in-depth knowledge on football-related topics. General Manager and Group Head of Sports for Cool FM, Wazobia FM, and Nigeria Info, Femi Obong-Daniels, disclosed that the “Femi and The Gang Fan Battle” provides football lovers with the opportunity to demonstrate their passion for the game. “Nigeria Info’s ‘Femi and The Gang Fan Battle’ is a sports-driven initiative that is primarily designed to promote the game of football in both entertaining and educating ways across the country. “The competition also serves as a unique platform that provides Nigerian youths with the chance to become renowned sportscasters, which invariably could position them as giants within the sports industry over time. “It is against this backdrop that we at Nigeria Info are embarking on this journey to provide sports-loving youths opportunity to make an impact by developing their passion points,” he said.
 
The ‘Femi and The Gang Fan Battle’ is a competition that seeks to strengthen the friendly sports ecosystem across the country by providing Nigerian youths with the opportunity to engage with one another through intelligent debates on the exciting game of football, while the winner clinches the grand prize of N1 million. The contest further aims to serve as a launch pad for a new generation of sports broadcasters who will raise the bar of sports journalism nationwide. 